# `components2/` directory contract

**Doctrine:** If this rule and `AGENTS.md` diverge, follow `AGENTS.md`. Shell-specific wiring: `.cursor/rules/shell-directory.mdc`.

**Import aliases:** `#components2/*` → `./components2/*` · `#app-shell` → `./components2/app-shell/index.ts` (server barrel) · `#app-shell/client` → `./components2/app-shell/client.ts`.

---

## Top-level folders (bounded context)

| Folder | Owns | Must not own |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `app-shell/` | Workbench chrome (RSC + client islands) | ERP/domain queries, feature business rules |
| `portal-shell/` | Portal chrome | Workbench shell, tenant truth |
| `stores/` | Context-free Zustand client stores | React providers, RSC, DB |
| `providers/` | Client React context/providers | Zustand stores, domain logic |
| `ui/` | Design-system primitives (shadcn shelf) | Feature workflows, shell layout |
| `metadata/` | Governed renderer kernel (ADR-0021) | ERP mutations |
| `auth/` | Pre-login auth UI — **Layer 3** (Card + client forms; see `_SEAL.md`) | Session guards, routes, metadata renderers |
| `dev/` | Gated local previews + fixtures | Production routes |
| `marketing/` | Public/marketing surfaces | ERP shell |

**Split rule:** stores and providers are **siblings** of `app-shell/`, not nested inside it. Shell components import stores via `#components2/stores` (or the `#app-shell/client` re-export when documented in `shell-directory.mdc`).

---

## File naming — read the filename

Goal: **without opening the file**, know **what it owns** and **what layer it is**. Names use **kebab-case nouns** chained left → right (general → specific). Length varies; every segment must earn its place.

### Pattern

```txt
[feature-prefix-]<entity>[-<aspect>].<layer>.ts(x)
```

| Part | Required? | Meaning | Example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `feature-prefix` | In crowded subfolders | Disambiguates files in the same folder | `appshell-` in `top-utils-bar/` |
| `entity` | Yes | The thing this file owns | `utility-bar`, `lane-memory`, `primary-left-rail` |
| `aspect` | Optional | A slice of the entity | `account-dropdown`, `network-diagnosis` |
| `layer` | Yes (except barrels) | File role — see table below | `.store`, `.client`, `.schema` |

**Folder = context.** Prefer short filenames inside a clearly named folder (`stores/utility-bar.store.ts`, not `stores/appshell-utility-bar.store.ts`).

### Layer suffixes (closed set)

| Suffix | Role | Primary export convention |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `.store.ts` | Zustand store (`"use client"`) | `use<Entity>Store` |
| `.provider.client.tsx` | Single React provider | `<Entity>Provider` |
| `.client.tsx` | Client component / island | PascalCase component matching entity |
| `.tsx` | RSC entry (`server-only`) or shared composition (no directive) | `AppShell`, `AppShellUtilityBar`, … |
| `.schema.ts` | Zod + `z.infer<>` types | Schema constants + inferred types |
| `.shared.ts` / `.shared.tsx` | Cross-layer types/helpers (no `"use client"` unless needed) | Named exports only |
| `.groups.ts` | Static menu/config blobs | Typed constants |
| `.fixture.ts` | Dev/test fixtures (`dev/fixtures/`) | Fixture constants |
| `index.ts` | Barrel for the folder | Re-exports only |

**Barrels:** `index.ts` / `client.ts` only — never put implementation in a barrel.

### Stores (`components2/stores/`) — reference practice

One store per file. **Domain first, `.store` last.**

```txt
<domain>.store.ts  →  use<DomainPascal>Store
```

| File | Hook / type door |
| --- | --- |
| `app-shell.store.ts` | `useAppShellStore` |
| `utility-bar.store.ts` | `useUtilityBarStore` |
| `lane-memory.store.ts` | `useLaneMemoryStore` |
| `operational-scope.store.ts` | `useOperationalScopeUiStore` |
| `utility-bar-catalog.shared.ts` | Catalog + ids (shared with app-shell UI, not a store) |
| `index.ts` | Re-exports all stores — no `create()` here |

Rules:

- **Domain** = state boundary (what UI surface or concern the store owns), kebab-case.
- Do **not** prefix store files with `appshell-` when the folder already scopes them (`stores/`).
- Persisted vs ephemeral is an implementation detail inside the file — not a filename segment.
- New shell UI state → new `<domain>.store.ts` + export from `stores/index.ts`; do not grow unrelated domains in one file.

### Providers (`components2/providers/`)

```txt
<what-it-provides>-provider.client.tsx
<feature>-providers.client.tsx          # composed bundle only
```

Examples: `theme-provider.client.tsx`, `sidebar-provider.client.tsx`, `app-shell-providers.client.tsx`.

**Rare:** `<domain>-store-provider.client.tsx` — only when a Zustand store must be **per-subtree** or **per-request** (factory + `useStore` from context per [Zustand Next.js guide](https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand/blob/main/docs/learn/guides/nextjs.md)). Default shell stores stay module singletons in `stores/` with **no** Zustand provider. Full rules: `.cursor/rules/client-state-management.mdc`.

### App shell (`components2/app-shell/`)

Subfolders name the **region**; files name the **piece**:

| Subfolder | Prefix on files | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `top-utils-bar/` | `appshell-utility-bar-` | `appshell-utility-bar-messenger.client.tsx` |
| `left-rail-bar/` | `appshell-primary-left-rail` | `appshell-primary-left-rail.schema.ts` |
| `surface/` | `appshell-sub-layout` | `appshell-sub-layout.client.tsx` |
| `crud-sap/` | `appshell-crud-sap-` | `appshell-crud-sap-action-bar.client.tsx` |
| Root of `app-shell/` | `appshell` | `appshell.tsx`, `appshell.client.tsx` |

RSC pair: `appshell.tsx` (public) + `appshell.client.tsx` (implementation). Types shared across the boundary → `appshell-props.shared.ts`.

### UI (`components2/ui/`)

Match shadcn slot names: `button.tsx`, `dropdown-menu.tsx`. No feature prefixes. Import only via `#components2/ui/<slot>`.

---

## Words to avoid in filenames

Do not use vague or banned bucket words (same spirit as `AGENTS.md` banned categories):

```txt
utils · helpers · manager · service · common · misc · temp · new · final · legacy · wrapper · stuff · data
```

Use a **concrete noun** instead: `utility-bar`, `lane-memory`, `viewport`, `operational-scope`.

---

## Forbidden filenames

```txt
schema.ts              → <entity>.schema.ts
shell.tsx              → appshell.tsx (or portal-shell.tsx)
store.ts               → <domain>.store.ts
index.ts with logic    → move impl to a named file
```

Generic single-word leaves inside `components2/` (`rail.tsx`, `surface.tsx` without qualifier) unless the folder has only one concept.

---

## Import boundaries

| Consumer | Import |
| --- | --- |
| RSC / server layouts | `#app-shell`, `#components2/ui/*` |
| Client shell islands | `#app-shell/client`, `#components2/stores`, `#components2/providers` |
| ERP features | `#components2/ui/*`, governed metadata via `#components2/metadata` — not deep `app-shell/` paths |

Client Components must not import `#app-shell` (server barrel). Stores are client-only — never import from RSC files.

---

## Checklist (new file)

1. Which folder owns this concept?
2. What is the **entity** (and optional **aspect**)?
3. Which **layer suffix** matches the export?
4. Does the filename map to the **primary export** without opening the file?
5. Are all segments concrete nouns (no banned words)?
